# Ad-hoc / one-shot scripts are local-only; only the checker + package marker
# (and this file) are tracked. Moved here from the root .gitignore
# ("backend/scripts/*"): ruff's gitignore-respecting walker (the `ignore`
# crate) misapplied that root-level glob to the app/ and tests/ walks when run
# from backend/, silently shrinking lint+format discovery to 4 files
# ("N files already formatted" with tiny N is the tell). A per-directory
# .gitignore only ever applies to walks inside scripts/, so git semantics are
# unchanged and ruff discovery is correct everywhere.
# (anki_archive/ predates the ignore rule and stays tracked; tracked files
# override gitignore. It remains outside ruff scope, same as CI today.)
*
!check_mock_boundaries.py
!__init__.py
!.gitignore
